It was a typical Monday morning at the office for John and his coworker, Emily. As John was sipping his coffee, he noticed that the office coffee machine was malfunctioning and spewing out a stream of water. Without hesitation, he quickly grabbed a nearby towel to clean up the mess. However, in his rush, he knocked over the towel, which fell on top of Emily's notes for an important presentation she was giving later that day.

Emily, being the perfectionist that she is, immediately assumed that John had deliberately ruined her notes. She stormed over to John's desk, pointed a shaking finger at him, and shouted, "You did this on purpose, didn't you?! You're always trying to sabotage my presentations!"

John was taken aback by Emily's outburst. He had no idea what was going on and thought they were talking about the malfunctioning coffee machine. He replied, "What are you talking about? I was just trying to clean up the mess! Why would I sabotage your presentation?"

Emily's face turned bright red with anger, and she shouted, "You're just trying to distract me from your incompetence! You're always late with your reports, and now you're messing up my notes!"

John couldn't take it anymore and shouted back, "That's it, I've had enough of your lies! I'm the one who's always on time, and I'm the one who's fixing this coffee machine right now!"

The argument escalated until their boss, Mrs. Johnson, walked into the office and saw the two colleagues standing in the middle of the room, shouting at each other. She stopped in her tracks, took a deep breath, and said, "What seems to be the problem here?"

John and Emily simultaneously pointed at each other, shouting, "He/She ruined my notes/ coffee machine!"

Mrs. Johnson looked at the situation and burst out laughing. "Oh dear, I think I see the problem. John, it seems you were trying to clean up the coffee machine, and Emily, it looks like your notes were in the way. And I think I see the cause of the problem..." Mrs. Johnson walked over to the coffee machine and flipped a switch. "Voila! The coffee machine was just stuck in an infinite loop of dispensing water. No one tried to sabotage anyone!"

John and Emily looked at each other, then at Mrs. Johnson, and then back at each other again. They both burst out laughing, and the argument was forgotten. From then on, they made sure to communicate more clearly before jumping to conclusions. And the office coffee machine was fixed.
